==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accomplished
<hw>Ac*com"plished</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Completed; effected; established; <as>as, an <ex>accomplished</ex>
fact</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Complete in acquirements as the result usually of
training; -- commonly in a good sense; <as>as, an <ex>accomplished</ex>
scholar, an <ex>accomplished</ex> villain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They . . . show themselves <qex>accomplished</qex> bees.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Daughter of God and man, <qex>accomplished</qex> Eve.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accomplisher</ent>⟦br⟧
